AKURE – The 33rd Olowo of Owo kingdom in Ondo State, Prince Ajibade Gbadegesin Ogunoye was on Friday installed. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Natives and residents of the town early in the morning trooped out in their thousands to witness the traditional rites ushering in the new Olowo. Addressing newsmen, the Ojumu of Owo, Chief Olanrewaju Famakinwa, revealed that the rites were in compliance with the customs and culture of the ancient town. Famakinwa disclosed that the new Olowo chose Sword of Peace in the course of the rite. He said: “Oba Ogunoye, who is being installed today, chose a sword which signifies peace. Traditionally, before a king is installed, he will have to choose a sword at Oke Mapo and it is believed that whichever one he chooses will tell how his reign will be. “Coincidentally, he choose the same sword chosen by his father more than 30 years ago and the sword represents sword.” Corroborating Chief Famakinwa, the Agbaomolowo, Chief Idowu Oludaye described the day as a good one for the ancient town because there was a new king. He described Oba Ogunoye as a man of honour, patience and humility, expressing hope that his reign would bring peace, prosperity and development to the town. Chief Oludaye implored the new monarch to accommodate all and sundry, soliciting for support of the residents for Oba Ogunoye who was selected as Olowo after polling 14 votes out of 15 on July 12, 2019 after the demise of the late Oba Victor Olateru- Olagbegi on April 18, 2019 at 77. He explained that disclosed that the coronation of the monarch would take place 17 days’ time.